fields.Title: BOOKSTORE / BACK DOOR
fields.Description: It's the back door of "Crime, Romance, and Biographies of Famous People". You can look at it, use a key object on it or try to force it open.

fields.Title: You: ""Please don't cry, please don't cry..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Please don't cry, please don't cry..." (Slap your face.) "I don't want anyone to see me cry!"

fields.Title: Warded Door: "After exerting some force you manag..."
fields.Dialogue Text: After exerting some force you manage to turn the key. It's eerily silent. The door slides slightly open, letting a draft of cold air into the room.

fields.Title: Shivers: "Outside, the wind howls in from acr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Outside, the wind howls in from across the bay. The building at Rue de Saint-Ghislaine stands like a matchbox on its side, with men inside like little wooden sticks ready to catch fire.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Walk it off, son! Stop wriggling li..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Walk it off, son! Stop wriggling like a maggot, it's nothing to worry about.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "That's right, take in your surround..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's right, take in your surroundings. You need to have a solid ground and a proper posture if you want to succeed.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "The door shudders with your impact...."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door shudders with your impact. Hinges snap, panels crack, splinters fly by as you smash through, tumbling into the darkness ahead.

fields.Title: Shivers: "You feel the tiny hairs on the back..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You feel the tiny hairs on the back of your neck rise up, as if someone's standing right behind you.

fields.Title: Warded Door: "It barely looks like you've done an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It barely looks like you've done any damage to the door, however -- it's still locked and closed, covered in dozens of little charms and trinkets.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Detective, you're the one in charg..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Detective, you're the one in charge." The lieutenant motions toward the door.

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""What is going *on* there?!" an ups..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What is going *on* there?!" an upset, high-pitched voice calls out from the bookstore. "Are you really trying to break down the back door?"

fields.Title: You: "And what about the door?"
fields.Dialogue Text: And what about the door?

fields.Title: You: ""Is that... Is that *blood* I'm see..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that... Is that *blood* I'm seeing?" (Rub your forehead.)

fields.Title: You: "Smash into the door and shout: "Wel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smash into the door and shout: "Welcome to Revachol!"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""You're not thinking of trying agai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're not thinking of trying again, are you?" The lieutenant stares at you as you stand there, silent and brooding.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Are you alright?" The lieutenant s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Are you alright?" The lieutenant steps closer, his eyes soft and worried. "This looked... pretty intense and painful, I must admit."

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""I warn you, don't tempt the spirit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I warn you, don't tempt the spirits, officer!" You can hear her take a frightened step backwards. "Don't tempt the spirits or you'll damage the holy *wards* on the door!"

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Steady breathing, solid core -- you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Steady breathing, solid core -- you've got this. With one shoulder forward you're ready to smash into the door like a battering ram.

fields.Title: Half Light: "An uneasy knot forms in the pit of..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An uneasy knot forms in the pit of your stomach...

fields.Title: You: "Break down the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Break down the door.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "Check your surroundings."
fields.Dialogue Text: Check your surroundings.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "A hollowed out, dark echo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A hollowed out, dark echo...

fields.Title: You: "Touch the back of your neck: What i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Touch the back of your neck: What is this feeling?

fields.Title: You: "Smash into the door again -- wordle..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smash into the door again -- wordless.

fields.Title: You: "Smash into the door and shout: "Han..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smash into the door and shout: "Hands up, now!"

fields.Title: You: ""Uh, Kim? Maybe you should go first..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Uh, Kim? Maybe you should go first..."

fields.Title: Warded Door: "A heavy door with a missing handle..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A heavy door with a missing handle stands before you, covered in dozens (if not hundreds) of Semenese trinkets and charms. It appears to be locked.

fields.Title: Warded Door: "Only an echo... No one is there."
fields.Dialogue Text: Only an echo... No one is there.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "It's made of a solid block of wood,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's made of a solid block of wood, but it has stood there for ages -- the hinges are old and coated with a carmine layer of rust. It should be doable.

fields.Title: You: "Maybe I *should* break it down? But..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe I *should* break it down? But not before I strategize...

fields.Title: You: "Smash into the door and shout: "Fuc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smash into the door and shout: "Fuck the system!"

fields.Title: Warded Door: "A heavy door with a missing handle..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A heavy door with a missing handle stands before you, covered in dozens (if not hundreds) of little oddly-shaped trinkets and charms. It appears to be locked.

fields.Title: You: ""Oh god..." (Try to breathe normall..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh god..." (Try to breathe normally.) "This really wasn't the best idea, was it..."

fields.Title: You: "Unlock the door with the key."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unlock the door with the key.

fields.Title: You: "Smash into the door and shout: "Fre..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smash into the door and shout: "Freeze, dirtbags!"

fields.Title: You: "First -- check your posture."
fields.Dialogue Text: First -- check your posture.

fields.Title: You: "Knock on the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock on the door.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "What if... you just break it down?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What if... you just break it down?

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""What are you doing, officer?!" A v..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What are you doing, officer?!" A voice rings from the other room. It sounds almost worried -- worried about your health.

fields.Title: Shivers: "A panicking woman squeezes the pend..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A panicking woman squeezes the pendant around her neck until it leaves a mark inside her palm. A man, a few metres away, stands frozen with a key in his hand. Somewhere inside a spider is spinning its web.

fields.Title: You: "Smash into the door and shout: "Fuc..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Smash into the door and shout: "Fuck, it hurts!"

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "You smash into the wood and see a s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You smash into the wood and see a small crack appear on the door frame. It's going to take one more try to break through to the other side, but you've done it...

fields.Title: You: ""I deserve this. My body deserves t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I deserve this. My body deserves to suffer for being this *weak* and *disappointing*."

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Ow, shoot! Whose moronic idea was i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ow, shoot! Whose moronic idea was it to just *run through the door*? Don't you know that things like that *hurt*?!

fields.Title: You: "[Open the door and enter.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Open the door and enter.]

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "The room is dimly lit and littered..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The room is dimly lit and littered with old barber shop rubbish, but the path to the door is clear.
